The paper deals with utilizing crowdsourcing for decision making tasks on micro-blog services, which involves algorithms and techniques for selecting a subset of crowd under a limited budget to minimize the probability of drawing a wrong answer. This problem is related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and social computing (cs.SI), as it involves utilizing human intelligence for decision making. The paper also discusses the individual error rates of the crowd, which is related to cybersecurity (cs.CY) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Finally, the paper involves studying the traits of JSP, which is related to social computing (cs.SOC).
